Clearly not. The creature was content to whistle and attempted to charge straight at Thassalin. Luckily, despite his size, he was agile enough to dodge, but Nyssi couldn't help but scream when she almost lost her grip on his too slippery scales.
"How do you kill them?", screamed Nyssi.
"How do you kill them!"
"How will you manage that?"
Thassalin panted, then circled around to approach the mountain he called his home. The dark beast followed, somewhat frantic when a flash of fire struck it from behind. The creature hadn't noticed it was no longer alone. Its panic grew when Thassalin slowed, then struck it violently on the head with his tail, causing it to veer off course.
Growling and hissing, the creature took to the altitude and spat into the air. Suddenly, everything turned black, as if the monster was sucking in the light of the sky and replacing it with a perpetual cloud of night.
Losing all visibility, Thassalin tried to retreat, but skimmed the treetops before crashing into the clearing. As if it had known exactly where he had fallen, the creature charged straight for him, dragging the dark cloud in its wake.
"Kayel!", exclaimed Tenuk as he emerged from the cloud and began to fly in circles to try and spot Nyssi and Thassalin below, in the darkness. "What are we doing, Kayel? Kayel...? Kayel, where are you?"
Below, Nyssi struggled to her feet. She was sure she had broken something, but her unnatural healing powers had already begun to take effect. As for Thassalin, he lay stretched out on a mound, propped against the only tree that hadn't buckled under his weight. Nyssi did her best to try and reach Thassalin, but she couldn't see two metres in front of her. Everything was plunged into darkness, swallowed by the impious shadows. And in those shadows, something was screaming.
A gruesome club-like tail comes crashing down beside Nyssi, knocking her over. She noted, however, that the tail was thrashing about, not targeting her. The creature, from what Nyssi could see and hear, was growling and swiping at the shadows it had created. Something teleported through the darkness, striking the monster and disorienting it.
A shot rang out suddenly, and the monster collapsed in silence, lifeless. The darkness surrounding them dissipated, revealing what had happened. Standing on the creature was Kayel, rifle in hand and panting for breath.
"It's... the strangest shadow jump I've ever made... Thanto kat'olon...", Kayel gasped. His eyes shone with a dark glow, and a somber energy coursed through his body. However, as he spoke, Kayel's organic plating regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow hue.
It took Nyssi a moment to understand what had happened. They all knew that Kayel had strange shadow powers, but he rarely used them because most people considered them impious and terrifying. Nyssi was unaware that Kayel could use those powers in the dark, and judging by his behavior, Kayel seemed just as surprised himself.
"Are you okay?", Nyssi couldn't help but ask.
"Yes, I'm fine. I killed something. It'll be better in a minute." Kayel examined his work, as Tenuk made his way to land beside him, resuming his normal form of Spast.
Now that the creature was still, they could see more clearly what it was. Its skin was black as coal and sticky, but the slime continued to adhere to its body. It had four wings and four limbs, all ending in long claws, and two straight horns protruded from its skull.
Before Tenuk and Kayel could ask what that thing was, something screamed and launched itself from a nearby bush. However, the beast didn't have time to reach them, as a familiar vehicle crashed into its side, sending it tumbling at Nyssi's feet. Not taking any chances, she grabbed her rifle and shot it in the head, killing the creature instantly.
"Oh no...", muttered Retvik from the driver's seat, before clumsily cutting off the engine and jumping out of the truck. "I, uh, didn't mean to do that. Are you alright?"
"You almost missed the whole action," Tenuk regretted. "Where were you?"
"Oh no, you all left me behind. I came here as fast as I could", sighed Retvik. "Can someone please tell us what these disgusting creatures are?"
Retvik's inquiry was fortunately answered by Thassalin, who had just gotten up. He was badly bruised and scratched all over and seemed a bit disoriented, but he didn't seem too badly hurt.
"YOU'VE KILLED THE CORRUPTIIDS! THE INFECTED MONSTERS. CREATURES LEFT BEHIND WHEN CORRUPTION ATTACKED YOUR GODS."
"Do you mean... the terrible god creature that we... helped kill?", stammered Tenuk.
"YES. JUST NOW. THERE MAY BE OTHERS, BUT I DIDN'T MANAGE TO HIT THEM ON THE HEAD. I'M MISSING A RIFLE. PLUS, TWO AGAINST ONE ISN'T FAIR, IS IT?"
"Uh... thanks... I guess", Kayel said with a shrug. "So, we're done here?"
Nyssi shrugged, then picked up her camera to take pictures of the beasts, now very much dead. She then pulled out her favorite dagger, the god of death's blade, and began to cut off one of the creature's horns, before moving on to the other. But just as she finished, the creatures ignited and quickly turned into piles of ashes. The same thing happened to the horns that Nyssi had cut off.
"Well, it's both convenient and not at all convenient," she sighed. "At least, I still have the photos..."
